<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.194555>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Cladistic analysis of the genus Nezara based on morphological characters. The most–parsimonious cladogram length 60 steps; consistency index 0,81; retention index 0,89. (․) non-homoplasious; (□) homoplasious. (In parentheses Bremer and Bootstrap values, respectively; Bootstrap values less than 50 omitted)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/194555/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.194556>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. A. Distribution map of Nezara species, based on the material examined in this work (except N. viridula) (the symbols correspond to the species - terminal taxa of the cladogram of Fig. 6B); B. Cladogram of Nezara (branches with Bremer support less than two steps collapsed).", "FIGURE 6. A. Distribution map of Nezara species, based on the material examined in this work (except N. viridula) (the symbols correspond to the species - terminal taxa of the cladogram of Fig. 6 B); B. Cladogram of Nezara (branches with Bremer support less than two steps collapsed)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/194556/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

